data.text:
Country: Kingdom of Sweden

King Gustaf VI Adolf (1950-1973)

Type: Non-circulating coin

Years: 1952

Value: 5 Kronor (5 SEK)

Currency: Krona (1873-date)

Composition: Silver (.400)

Weight: 22.88 g.

Diameter: 36 mm

Thickness: 2.5 mm

Grade: AU58

Shape: Round

Mintage: 242,241

Demonetized: Yes, 06-30-2017

References: KM# 828

Commemorative issue:

70th Anniversary of the Birth of Gustav VI Adolf.

Obverse:

Head of King Gustaf VI Adolf facing left. Engraver's initials below neck.

Lettering:

GUSTAF VI ADOLF SVERIGES KONUNG

Translation: Gustaf VI Adolf King of Sweden.

Engraver: Léo Holmgren.

Reverse:

Crowned King's Monogram divides value at sides. Above there is the date of the birthday anniversary with at sides the mark of Stockholm Mint (at left) and the initials of the Governor of the Riksbank (at right).

Lettering:

11 · XI 1952 TS

5 GAVI KR

SVENSK · ODLINGS · BEFRÄMJARE

Translation:

11 November 1952

5 (Monogram) KRONER

SWEDISH CULTURE PROMOTER

Engraver: Léo Holmgren.

Edge:

Smooth.

Reference : KM# 828

Source : https://www.ngccoin.com/price-guide/worl...
